2026-05-02 23:06:44 | INFO     | BookTranslator.translator.Translaton_Chain:run:30 - Traditional Issues  
General large models lack real-time perception of space and time, making it difficult to directly understand the user's current location, speed, direction, and the surrounding environment, often resulting in responses that are out of context.  

Dynamic Route Feedback  
By using multiplexing and sentence segmentation to identify keywords like "take me to" or "navigate to," the system no longer enters the general casual chat chain. Instead, it directly switches to the navigation state machine, significantly reducing the response time for the first character and converting long texts from the large model into short, broadcastable instructions in real time.  

Before the voice is sent to the large model, the system injects the user's GPS coordinates, movement speed, direction information, and real-time visual recognition results from the front. This upgrades the AI from a "general chat" assistant to a "space-time perception assistant" tailored for the visually impaired navigation scenario.
