2026-05-02 23:55:42 | INFO     | BookTranslator.translator.Translaton_Chain:run:30 - Traditional Issues  
General large models lack real-time spatial awareness, making it difficult to directly understand the visually impaired user's current location, speed, direction, and surrounding environment, often leading to context-inappropriate responses.  

Dynamic Route Echoing  
By using multiplexing and sentence segmentation to identify keywords like "take me to" or "navigate to," the system no longer enters a general casual chat chain but directly switches to a navigation state machine, significantly reducing the time to first character response.  

Before voice input reaches the large model, the system injects real-time GPS coordinates, movement speed, direction information, and visual recognition results of the user's surroundings. This upgrades the AI from a "general chatbot" to a "spatial awareness assistant tailored for obstacle-avoidance scenarios."
