2026-05-02 23:58:22 | INFO     | BookTranslator.translator.Translaton_Chain:run:30 - NCNN/OpenVINO INT8 PTQ  
Quantization essentially uses a small amount of calibration data to determine the range and calculate the scaling factor (scale).  
Actual tests show that after INT8 quantization, the model size is drastically compressed to just 3.4MB. On the Raspberry Pi 5, single-frame inference latency drops from over 200ms to 40ms (a 4-5x speedup), perfectly meeting the real-time obstacle avoidance requirements on the edge.
