2026-05-03 12:53:14 | INFO     | BookTranslator.translator.Translaton_Chain:run:30 - Traditional Issues  
General large models lack real-time spatial awareness, making it difficult to directly understand the blind or visually impaired user's current location, speed, direction, and the surrounding environment, often resulting in responses disconnected from the actual scene.  

Dynamic Route Echoing  
By utilizing multiplexing and sentence segmentation to recognize keywords such as "take me to" or "navigate to," the system bypasses the general conversation chain and directly enters the navigation state machine.  
Converts long text from the large model into short, broadcastable instructions in real time, significantly reducing the response time for the first word.  

Before feeding the voice into the large model, the system injects the user's GPS coordinates, movement speed, direction, and real-time visual recognition results from the environment. This upgrades the AI from a "general chatbot" to a "spatial awareness assistant for blind navigation scenarios."
