2026-05-03 12:55:25 | INFO     | BookTranslator.translator.Translaton_Chain:run:30 - Traditional Issues  
General-purpose large models lack real-time awareness of time and space, making it difficult to directly understand the visually impaired user's current location, speed, and orientation, as well as the surrounding environment ahead. This often leads to replies that are disconnected from the actual context.  

Dynamic Route Echoing  
By utilizing multiplexing and sentence segmentation to identify keywords such as "take me to" or "navigate to," the system no longer enters the general-purpose chat loop. Instead, it directly transitions into the navigation state machine, significantly reducing the time to the first word response.  

Before the voice input is processed by the large model, the system injects the user's GPS coordinates, speed, orientation information, and forward visual recognition results in real-time. This upgrades the AI from a "general-purpose chat" system to a "spatiotemporal awareness assistant for guide-dog scenarios."  

Real-Time Conversion of Long Text to Broadcastable Short Commands  
The system converts long text from the large model into short, broadcastable commands in real-time.
