2026-05-03 12:57:25 | INFO     | BookTranslator.translator.Translaton_Chain:run:30 - Traditional Issues  
General large models lack real-time spatiotemporal awareness, making it difficult to directly understand a visually impaired person's current location, speed, direction, and the surrounding environment, often leading to responses that are detached from the context.  

Dynamic Route Echo  
By utilizing multiplexing and sentence segmentation to identify keywords such as "take me to" or "navigate to," the system avoids entering the general casual dialogue chain. Instead, it directly switches to the navigation state machine, significantly reducing the first-word response time by converting long text from large models into short, broadcast-friendly instructions in real time.  

Before the voice is sent to the large model, the system injects the user's GPS coordinates, movement speed, direction, and front-facing visual recognition results in real time, upgrading the AI from a "general chat" tool to a "spatiotemporal-aware assistant for blind navigation scenarios."
