2026-05-03 14:34:25 | INFO     | BookTranslator.translator.Translaton_Chain:run:30 - Traditional Issues
General large models lack real-time spatiotemporal awareness, making it difficult to directly understand the current location, speed, direction, and surrounding environment of visually impaired individuals, often leading to responses detached from the actual scenario.

Dynamic Route Echoing
Through multiplexing and segmentation, keywords such as "take me to" or "navigate to" are identified. Instead of entering the general casual conversation chain, the system directly switches to the navigation state machine, significantly reducing the time for the first word response and converting long text from the large model into short, broadcastable commands in real time.

Before the speech is fed into the large model, the system injects the user's GPS coordinates, movement speed, direction, and front-view visual recognition results in real time, upgrading the AI from "general conversation" to a "spatiotemporal-aware assistant for obstacle avoidance navigation scenarios."
